# trusted-numbers.conf — Whitelist of phone numbers paired treats as trusted.
#
# Copy to ~/.config/paired/trusted-numbers.conf and edit.
# Used by:
#   - paired-call-handler   — decides whether to ignore/notify/hangup an incoming call
#   - paired-respond        — decides whether to invoke the LLM trigger
#   - paired-sms-command-hook — decides whether to honour /phone <num> <msg> Tasker speak
#
# UK number normalization: any of "07XXXXXXXXX", "+44 7XXXXXXXXX", "00447XXXXXXXXX",
# "447XXXXXXXXX" match the same entry. International numbers should be in E.164 form.
#
# Format:   <number> [#optional comment]
# Comments: # at start of line, blank lines OK
# Lookup:   paired-trusted list / paired-trusted add <num> [label] / paired-trusted remove <num>

# === Examples (replace with your own) ===

# 07911123456          # main mobile  ← Ofcom drama-reserved example only
# +14155552671         # US E.164 example
# 07911123457          # work line
# 07911123458          # partner

# === Live entries ===
# (Add yours below this line)
